## Normal Mode

 0  beginning of line
 $  end of line
 u  undo
 x  delete char
 dd delete line   (put in clipboard)
 dj del 2 line
 dw del till end of the word
 hjkl  move cursor like arrow left  down  up right
 p  paste text
 gg beginning of file
 G  end of a file
 yy copy line

C r replace char

## Insert Mode

i = insert mode
I = insert mode from begining
a = insert mode end of char
A = insert mode + goto end of current line
esc = normal mode

## Command Mode

:q quit
:wq write quit
:q! quit without saving
:r filename insert file content
:w filename  write to filenmae
:! Llinux command  Execute linux commands
:e edit new file
:enew  new file
:bp previous file open in buffer
:bn next file open in buffer
:bd close file
:badd filename (open file as not active)
:%s/searchtext/relacetext/g  Find and replace
:set number (line number)
:set nonumber
up,down  prevvious command

## visual mode

v         Character-wise visual mode
V         Line-wise visual mode
arrow select text
y copy selected and exit to normal mode
esc = normal mode
:sort ui  (sort selected lines)

## split view

:split,:sp file
^+ww  switch file
:vsplit,:vs filename (vertical split)
You can open same file with split

